                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/8190c</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in Certain Countries</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d122fn1">Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Costa
                        Rica, Cuba, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, Guatemala, Haiti, Honduras, Mexico,
                        Nicaragua, Panama, Paraguay, and Peru.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-25T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confer with Allied colleagues before recommending changes in enemy trading list.
                    If agreement results from conference, report decision and reasons. If
                    disagreement results, send your opinion and variant opinions of colleagues with
                    reasons. In each case give <pb facs="0186" n="1020" xml:id="pg_1020"/>
                    nationality and residence of person or association recommended for addition or
                    removal from list. Repeat to consuls.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
